  "body": "#### System information\r\nerigon version 2022.09.1-alpha-4067b7c4\r\n\r\nKubernetes image\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nFrom what I understand 2 ETH static block reward is no longer attributed to the miner post merge. At least that is what Etherscan is showing:\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\nBlock Reward:\r\n0.042817389981615504 Ether (0 + 0.163373401868959011 - 0.120556011887343507)\r\n```\r\n\r\nhttps://etherscan.io/block/15552012\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nThe following request:\r\n\r\n`curl http://erigon-hz.production.san:30250 -X POST   -H \"Content-Type: application/json\"   --data '{\"method\":\"trace_filter\",\"params\":[{\"fromBlock\":\"0xED4E0C\",\"toBlock\":\"0xED4E0C\"}],\"id\":1,\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\"}'`\r\n\r\nwould return:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n  {\r\n      \"action\": {\r\n          \"author\": \"0xb73b4941c872d75c61e9986aef51f8def14c6c63\",\r\n          \"rewardType\": \"block\",\r\n          \"value\": \"0x1bc16d674ec80000\"\r\n      },\r\n      \"blockHash\": \"0x9395804cd3a1632b1a6661c1096b29d993a237131d28fd0236b3e0b0d9daffb1\",\r\n      \"blockNumber\": 15552012,\r\n      \"result\": null,\r\n      \"subtraces\": 0,\r\n      \"traceAddress\": [],\r\n      \"type\": \"reward\"\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo my question is should this 'reward' trace be returned in the first place and if so, should it be attributed to the miner, does the miner receive those funds?\r\n",
